Henry’s law finds several applications in industry and explains some biological phenomena.", "fibs": ["x"]}
{"text": "Notable among these are:


To increase the solubility of CO2 in soft drinks and soda water, the bottle is sealed under high pressure.", "fibs": ["increase"]}
{"text": "Scuba divers must cope with high concentrations of dissolved gases while breathing air at high pressure underwater.", "fibs": ["Scuba"]}
{"text": "Increased pressure increases the solubility of atmospheric gases in blood.", "fibs": ["pressure"]}
{"text": "When the divers come towards surface, the pressure gradually decreases.", "fibs": ["surface"]}
{"text": "This releases the dissolved gases and leads to the formation of bubbles of nitrogen in the blood.", "fibs": ["formation"]}
{"text": "This blocks capillaries and creates a medical condition known as bends, which are painful and dangerous to life.", "fibs": ["condition"]}
{"text": "To avoid bends, as well as, the toxic effects of high concentrations of nitrogen in the blood, the tanks used by scuba divers are filled with air diluted with helium (11.7% helium, 56.2% nitrogen and 32.1% oxygen).", "fibs": ["nitrogen"]}
{"text": "At high altitudes the partial pressure of oxygen is less than that at the ground level.", "fibs": ["pressure"]}
{"text": "This leads to low concentrations of oxygen in the blood and tissues of people living at high altitudes or climbers.", "fibs": ["oxygen"]}
{"text": "Low blood oxygen causes climbers to become weak and unable to think clearly, symptoms of a condition known as anoxia.", "fibs": ["blood"]}
{"text": "Effect of Temperature


      Solubility of gases in liquids decreases with rise in temperature.", "fibs": ["Effect"]}
{"text": "When dissolved, the gas molecules are present in liquid phase and the process of dissolution can be considered similar to condensation and heat is evolved in this process.", "fibs": ["gas"]}
{"text": "We have learnt in the last Section that dissolution process involves dynamic equilibrium and thus must follow Le Chatelier’s Principle.", "fibs": ["learnt"]}
{"text": "As dissolution is an exothermic process, the solubility should decrease with increase of temperature.", "fibs": ["dissolution"]}
