2.6.2 Elevation of Boiling Point
We have learnt in Unit 5, Class XI, that the vapour pressure of a liquid increases with increase of temperature.", "fibs": ["p10"]}
{"text": "It boils at the temperature at which its vapour pressure is equal to the atmospheric pressure.", "fibs": ["temperature"]}
{"text": "For example, water boils at 373.15 K (100° C) because at this temperature the vapour pressure of water is 1.013 bar (1 atmosphere).", "fibs": ["example"]}
{"text": "We have also learnt in the last section that vapour pressure of the solvent decreases in the presence of non-volatile solute.", "fibs": ["learnt"]}
{"text": "Fig.", "fibs": ["Fig"]}
