{"text": "A raw mango placed in concentrated salt solution loses water via osmosis and shrivel into pickle.", "fibs": ["mango"]}
{"text": "Wilted flowers revive when placed in fresh water.", "fibs": ["water"]}
{"text": "A carrot that has become limp because of water loss into the atmosphere can be placed into the water making it firm once again.", "fibs": ["carrot"]}
{"text": "Water will move into its cells through osmosis.", "fibs": ["move"]}
{"text": "When placed in water containing less than 0.9% (mass/volume) salt, blood cells swell due to flow of water in them by osmosis.", "fibs": ["water"]}
{"text": "People taking a lot of salt or salty food experience water retention in tissue cells and intercellular spaces because of osmosis.", "fibs": ["lot"]}
{"text": "The resulting puffiness or swelling is called edema.", "fibs": ["puffiness"]}
{"text": "Water movement from soil into plant roots and subsequently into upper portion of the plant is partly due to osmosis.", "fibs": ["movement"]}
{"text": "The preservation of meat by salting and of fruits by adding sugar protects against bacterial action.", "fibs": ["preservation"]}
{"text": "Through the process of osmosis, a bacterium on salted meat or candid fruit loses water, shrivels and dies.", "fibs": ["process"]}
{"text": "2.6.5 Reverse Osmosis and Water Purification
The direction of osmosis can be reversed if a pressure larger than the osmotic pressure is applied to the solution side.", "fibs": ["Purification"]}
{"text": "That is, now the pure solvent flows out of the solution through the semi permeable membrane.", "fibs": ["solution"]}
{"text": "This phenomenon is called reverse osmosis and is of great practical utility.", "fibs": ["phenomenon"]}
{"text": "Reverse osmosis is used in desalination of sea water.", "fibs": ["osmosis"]}
{"text": "A schematic set up for the process is shown in Fig.", "fibs": ["process"]}
{"text": "When pressure more than osmotic pressure is applied, pure water is squeezed out of the sea water through the membrane.", "fibs": ["pressure"]}
{"text": "A variety of polymer membranes are available for this purpose.", "fibs": ["variety"]}
{"text": "Fig.", "fibs": ["Fig"]}
{"text": "2.11: Reverse osmosis occurs when a pressure larger than the osmotic pressure is applied to the solution.", "fibs": ["osmosis"]}
{"text": "The pressure required for the reverse osmosis is quite high.", "fibs": ["pressure"]}
{"text": "A workable porous membrane is a film of cellulose acetate placed over a suitable support.", "fibs": ["membrane"]}
{"text": "Cellulose acetate is permeable to water but impermeable to impurities and ions present in sea water.", "fibs": ["Cellulose"]}
{"text": "These days many countries use desalination plants to meet their potable water requirements.", "fibs": ["use"]}
